A rhetorical question implying a negative opinion on the part of the speaker.—Compare the speech here assigned to Manlius with Horace, iii., ode ὅ, 12. The similarity is too great to be accidental, and Livy's display of rhetoric, like Horace's ode, may have been intended to influence opinion about the recovery of the soldiers of Crassus and Antony, who had been so long the prisoners of the Parthians.
